01:22:03,669 --> 01:22:06,546
♪ I will walk where my steps take me ♪

1319
01:22:06,547 --> 01:22:11,134
♪ And let the rain wash away
These feelings of mine ♪

1320
01:22:11,135 --> 01:22:13,137
[siren wailing]

1321
01:22:15,681 --> 01:22:18,433
♪ Endlessly, aimlessly ♪

1322
01:22:18,434 --> 01:22:22,229
♪ My heart is floating
Here and there in the rain ♪

1323
01:22:27,777 --> 01:22:31,071
♪ The passersby don't know ♪

1324
01:22:31,072 --> 01:22:33,990
♪ The lonely streetlights don't know ♪

1325
01:22:33,991 --> 01:22:36,743
♪ The dizzying mass of days long gone ♪

1326
01:22:36,744 --> 01:22:40,623
♪ Like a flower bed bursting
Recklessly into bloom ♪

1327
01:22:44,335 --> 01:22:47,337
♪ I will walk where my steps take me ♪

1328
01:22:47,338 --> 01:22:51,342
♪ And let the rain wash away
These feelings of mine ♪

1329
01:22:56,347 --> 01:22:59,140
♪ Endlessly, aimlessly ♪

1330
01:22:59,141 --> 01:23:03,562
♪ My heart is floating
Here and there in the rain ♪

1331
01:23:19,662 --> 01:23:22,123
[yawns]

1332
01:23:29,505 --> 01:23:30,631
[grunts]

1333
01:23:33,050 --> 01:23:34,802
[sighs]

1334
01:23:37,138 --> 01:23:38,347
[Miri] Honey.

1335
01:23:38,889 --> 01:23:40,014
Honey.

1336
01:23:40,015 --> 01:23:41,642
- Honey!
- [Hm?

1337
01:23:44,270 --> 01:23:45,896
[whispering] The police are here.

1338
01:23:51,402 --> 01:23:52,862
What should we do?

1339
01:24:00,661 --> 01:24:03,079
Be sure not to panic, okay?

1340
01:24:03,080 --> 01:24:04,623
I need to change clothes.

1341
01:24:09,295 --> 01:24:11,297
- [ominous music playing]
- [resigned sigh]

1342
01:24:14,133 --> 01:24:16,302
I'll explain it all at the station.

1343
01:24:18,053 --> 01:24:19,054
It's all my--

1344
01:24:19,555 --> 01:24:20,848
You Si-one.

1345
01:24:22,224 --> 01:24:23,392
What were you saying?

1346
01:24:26,479 --> 01:24:30,858
It's all my fault for being a bad father.

1347
01:24:49,710 --> 01:24:51,712
[inaudible]

1348
01:24:54,089 --> 01:24:55,925
You're the one who said not to panic!

1349
01:24:58,719 --> 01:24:59,804
Get in!

1350
01:25:01,514 --> 01:25:02,639
[engine starts]

1351
01:25:02,640 --> 01:25:03,891
[Man-su] The door...

1352
01:25:04,850 --> 01:25:06,852
[line ringing]

1353
01:25:10,689 --> 01:25:13,108
[Miri] Is Dongho's mom
not picking up on purpose?

1354
01:25:14,193 --> 01:25:17,196
How could Dongho
rat on his friend like that?

1355
01:25:18,072 --> 01:25:21,658
It can't have been Si-one's idea.

1356
01:25:21,659 --> 01:25:25,078
It's Dongho's dad's store.
So Dongho suggested it.

1357
01:25:25,079 --> 01:25:26,329
Isn't it obvious?

1358
01:25:26,330 --> 01:25:28,248
- DONGHO'S MOM
- [line ringing]

1359
01:25:28,249 --> 01:25:30,251
[voicemail message plays]

1360
01:25:32,211 --> 01:25:35,214
He must be so lonely
and scared, my baby.

1361
01:25:35,923 --> 01:25:37,466
This is all your fault!

1362
01:25:41,554 --> 01:25:42,555
Excuse me!

1363
01:25:45,891 --> 01:25:48,185
Just a minute! Wait!

1364
01:25:49,395 --> 01:25:50,688
Hold on a minute!

1365
01:25:51,772 --> 01:25:54,650
Listen, his mother is parking the car.

1366
01:25:55,234 --> 01:25:58,695
Can we go in with him?
He's still just a kid.

1367
01:25:58,696 --> 01:26:00,990
- [officer] All right.
- Thank you.

1368
01:26:01,949 --> 01:26:03,909
Lift your head. Look at me.

1369
01:26:04,743 --> 01:26:07,830
Dongho dragged you into it, right?

1370
01:26:08,497 --> 01:26:09,540
Dongho?

1371
01:26:10,457 --> 01:26:11,583
Why would he drag me--

1372
01:26:11,584 --> 01:26:14,628
Hey. Listen...

1373
01:26:15,880 --> 01:26:20,676
Doing a crime on your own
is incredibly lonely and scary.

1374
01:26:21,427 --> 01:26:23,554
That's how I imagine it, anyway.

1375
01:26:25,973 --> 01:26:28,308
I'll never leave you to feel lonely.

1376
01:26:28,309 --> 01:26:30,727
So, I need your cooperation.

1377
01:26:30,728 --> 01:26:32,271
Since we're a team.

1378
01:26:36,942 --> 01:26:39,193
Actually, the one who suggested it—

1379
01:26:39,194 --> 01:26:42,030
Hey, hey, wait. Wait!

1380
01:26:42,031 --> 01:26:43,281
Get a grip.

1381
01:26:43,282 --> 01:26:44,450
Listen to me.

1382
01:26:45,159 --> 01:26:47,702
Our family is in a war now.

1383
01:26:47,703 --> 01:26:48,703
What?

1384
01:26:48,704 --> 01:26:51,290
No, I don't mean with each other.

1385
01:26:51,916 --> 01:26:53,875
[groaning]

1386
01:26:53,876 --> 01:26:59,088
You and me, in this war,
we need to protect our women, right?

1387
01:26:59,089 --> 01:27:00,758
You know Grandpa's pistol?

1388
01:27:01,842 --> 01:27:04,761
Your grandpa bent the fingers
of a dead Viet Cong

1389
01:27:04,762 --> 01:27:07,264
and took that pistol, why do you think?

1390
01:27:08,390 --> 01:27:14,563
To remember that if he hadn't shot first,
the enemy would've shot him with that gun.

1391
01:27:15,522 --> 01:27:16,899
You get what I mean?

1392
01:27:26,533 --> 01:27:28,535
[Ri-one humming]

1393
01:27:29,453 --> 01:27:31,455
[Ri-one urinating and humming]

1394
01:27:43,300 --> 01:27:44,802
All the men...

1395
01:27:45,552 --> 01:27:48,013
What'll you do, huh?

1396
01:27:50,933 --> 01:27:52,935
[toilet flushing]

1397
01:27:55,521 --> 01:27:57,438
[yawns]

1398
01:27:57,439 --> 01:27:58,816
Let's wash your hands.

1399
01:28:02,444 --> 01:28:03,612
Up you go!

1400
01:28:09,827 --> 01:28:15,791
Dongho says Si-one wanted to sell
the phones and help out his mom. Damn!

1401
01:28:18,752 --> 01:28:21,504
It's your own store.

1402
01:28:21,505 --> 01:28:23,507
Let's put this behind us.

1403
01:28:24,925 --> 01:28:25,968
[scoffs]

1404
01:28:38,772 --> 01:28:42,067
If you don't settle,
he'll get a year's sentence.

1405
01:28:42,651 --> 01:28:46,280
A mom can't let that happen to her son.

1406
01:28:47,072 --> 01:28:48,198
Isn't that so?

1407
01:28:50,576 --> 01:28:51,910
[grunts]

1408
01:28:52,911 --> 01:28:54,997
Hey, Man-su.

1409
01:28:55,789 --> 01:28:57,206
Wonno.

1410
01:28:57,207 --> 01:28:58,459
Gimme a smoke.

1411
01:28:59,418 --> 01:29:00,544
Sure.

1412
01:29:01,920 --> 01:29:03,839
What are you doing?

1413
01:29:04,381 --> 01:29:06,550
I started smoking again.

1414
01:29:13,390 --> 01:29:16,977
But honey, mind if I talk
to my friend for a sec?

1415
01:29:17,936 --> 01:29:19,104
Just talk.

1416
01:29:20,022 --> 01:29:21,523
You don't mind, do you?

1417
01:29:23,150 --> 01:29:24,525
Well...

1418
01:29:24,526 --> 01:29:25,903
Mm-mm.

1419
01:29:26,528 --> 01:29:28,197
Mm-mm.

1420
01:29:30,157 --> 01:29:35,162
Dongho dragged Si-one into it.
That's what Dongho will testify.

1421
01:29:35,954 --> 01:29:37,831
Si-one just stood nearby.

1422
01:29:38,582 --> 01:29:39,665
What a crock of shit!

1423
01:29:39,666 --> 01:29:42,127
Dongho turned off the CCTV,

1424
01:29:43,879 --> 01:29:45,380
but not the other one.

1425
01:29:46,840 --> 01:29:49,759
He didn't know to turn off
the security system.

1426
01:29:49,760 --> 01:29:52,095
What if your wife found out

1427
01:29:52,096 --> 01:29:56,182
you use that store at night
as a place for fucking women?

1428
01:29:56,183 --> 01:30:02,271
And if she heard you bragged about it
to all the men in the neighborhood?

1429
01:30:02,272 --> 01:30:05,733
You jobless stinking piece of shit!

1430
01:30:05,734 --> 01:30:08,069
- I'll fucking kill you!
- [Miri exclaims]

1431
01:30:08,070 --> 01:30:09,238
One more thing.

1432
01:30:09,863 --> 01:30:11,615
You're not buying my home.

1433
01:30:12,324 --> 01:30:13,158
Miri, let's go.

1434
01:30:16,912 --> 01:30:18,788
Forget buying it.

1435
01:30:18,789 --> 01:30:20,290
Honey, be careful.

1436
01:30:26,672 --> 01:30:29,215
Are they up there?

1437
01:30:29,216 --> 01:30:31,051
Huh? Are there many?

1438
01:30:34,346 --> 01:30:35,514
How many? [grunts]

1439
01:30:37,015 --> 01:30:38,058
There's more?

1440
01:30:40,185 --> 01:30:41,102
[mutters]

1441
01:30:41,103 --> 01:30:42,728
That brat...

1442
01:30:42,729 --> 01:30:44,648
Two, four, six...

1443
01:30:48,569 --> 01:30:50,320
We don't have to give them back?

1444
01:30:51,155 --> 01:30:52,739
Let's make them disappear.

1445
01:30:53,365 --> 01:30:56,868
Wonno can't help but cover it up anyway.

1446
01:30:56,869 --> 01:30:58,745
- Right?
- Of course.

1447
01:31:01,331 --> 01:31:03,125
- [grunts]
- Oh.

1448
01:31:07,087 --> 01:31:09,589
[Miri grunting]

1449
01:31:09,590 --> 01:31:11,592
[Man-su grunting]

1450
01:31:13,677 --> 01:31:15,511
What tree will you plant?

1451
01:31:15,512 --> 01:31:17,889
[Man-su] When the apples ripen,
let's make jam.

1452
01:31:17,890 --> 01:31:19,265
[Ri-one plucking cello strings]

1453
01:31:19,266 --> 01:31:21,601
[Si-one] Will the roots grow
over the phones?

1454
01:31:21,602 --> 01:31:24,187
[Man-su] The tastiest things
grow on filth.

1455
01:31:24,188 --> 01:31:26,773
Fertilizer's made from shit and piss.

1456
01:31:31,612 --> 01:31:34,072
Okay, thank you.

1457
01:31:36,158 --> 01:31:38,994
Is it true about Grandpa?

1458
01:31:40,245 --> 01:31:42,289
He hanged himself in this house?

1459
01:31:46,293 --> 01:31:47,794
You know his pig farm?

1460
01:31:48,712 --> 01:31:50,422
They caught a disease,

1461
01:31:51,173 --> 01:31:54,091
and he had to kill them all,
20,000 pigs.

1462
01:31:54,092 --> 01:31:56,385
[gasps] How?

1463
01:31:56,386 --> 01:31:58,096
He buried them alive.

1464
01:31:59,514 --> 01:32:02,391
But he was always a bit unstable.

1465
01:32:02,392 --> 01:32:04,852
Ever since fighting in Vietnam.

1466
01:32:04,853 --> 01:32:06,646
In the old barn, he...

1467
01:32:06,647 --> 01:32:10,150
You know... but I didn't see it.

1468
01:32:12,194 --> 01:32:14,029
Oh. Hey.

1469
01:32:18,325 --> 01:32:19,576
Sit with me.

1470
01:32:20,202 --> 01:32:21,286
Come closer.

1471
01:32:22,037 --> 01:32:24,039
[tense music playing]

1472
01:32:30,003 --> 01:32:31,380
Mom doesn't know.

1473
01:32:32,464 --> 01:32:33,966
Don't look, don't look!

1474
01:32:35,884 --> 01:32:37,094
I quit.

1475
01:32:39,304 --> 01:32:40,806
Throw them out yourself.

1476
01:33:26,560 --> 01:33:27,436
[gags]

1477
01:33:29,104 --> 01:33:31,106
[sighs]

1478
01:34:10,103 --> 01:34:12,105
[buzzing]

1479
01:34:16,943 --> 01:34:17,986
- [buzzing stops]
- [grunts]

1480
01:34:23,158 --> 01:34:25,160
[whimpering softly]

1481
01:34:27,287 --> 01:34:29,289
[buzzing]

1482
01:34:31,124 --> 01:34:33,126
- [whimpering softly]
- [buzzing stops]

1483
01:34:41,802 --> 01:34:42,928
[exhales]

1484
01:34:56,691 --> 01:34:58,693
[scissors snipping]

1485
01:35:01,363 --> 01:35:02,197
[grunts]

1486
01:35:17,629 --> 01:35:19,631
[grunting softly]

1487
01:35:54,499 --> 01:35:55,333
[grunts]

1488
01:36:05,635 --> 01:36:06,595
[groans]

1489
01:36:08,513 --> 01:36:10,515
[whimpering]

1490
01:36:17,731 --> 01:36:18,815
[man] Papyrus...

1491
01:36:19,941 --> 01:36:21,485
You interviewed there?

1492
01:36:23,528 --> 01:36:24,695
I was rejected.

1493
01:36:24,696 --> 01:36:27,407
- The name Go Sijo--
- Never heard of it.

1494
01:36:33,580 --> 01:36:34,998
And Gu Bummo?

1495
01:36:41,213 --> 01:36:42,671
Uh...

1496
01:36:42,672 --> 01:36:43,632
Not sure...

1497
01:36:44,466 --> 01:36:47,301
We're visiting people
who interviewed there.

1498
01:36:47,302 --> 01:36:49,595
Anything unusual happen recently?

1499
01:36:49,596 --> 01:36:51,264
Have you felt in danger?

1500
01:36:55,435 --> 01:36:58,020
Those two men have disappeared.

1501
01:36:58,021 --> 01:36:59,648
[exhales]

1502
01:37:00,899 --> 01:37:02,566
You may think badly of me,

1503
01:37:02,567 --> 01:37:04,903
but even after hearing they died,

1504
01:37:05,445 --> 01:37:10,574
the thought that comes to mind is,
I wonder what lucky person got hired?

1505
01:37:10,575 --> 01:37:11,952
I said "disappeared."

1506
01:37:12,786 --> 01:37:13,786
Give me that.

1507
01:37:13,787 --> 01:37:15,871
And then,

1508
01:37:15,872 --> 01:37:21,670
Mr. You, you said to me, "They died."

1509
01:37:22,963 --> 01:37:24,965
Why do you think they're dead?

1510
01:37:25,840 --> 01:37:27,217
Well...

1511
01:37:28,593 --> 01:37:32,054
In today's world, if someone disappears,

1512
01:37:32,055 --> 01:37:33,431
then usually...

1513
01:37:35,100 --> 01:37:39,395
"In today's world,
if someone disappears...

1514
01:37:39,396 --> 01:37:40,688
- [gulps]
- ...then usually..."

1515
01:37:40,689 --> 01:37:44,316
Go Sijo's wife reported him missing,

1516
01:37:44,317 --> 01:37:48,445
and after tracking his phone,
we found his car sitting by itself.

1517
01:37:48,446 --> 01:37:51,657
She said after being fired,
he was extremely depressed.

1518
01:37:51,658 --> 01:37:52,658
Oh, my.

1519
01:37:52,659 --> 01:37:56,245
A phone contains
all of a person's life, right?

1520
01:37:56,246 --> 01:37:57,955
Who you talked to,

1521
01:37:57,956 --> 01:38:00,667
and also, who you couldn't talk to.

1522
01:38:01,334 --> 01:38:02,876
- 9 MISSED CALLS
- [ringing]

1523
01:38:02,877 --> 01:38:04,004
What the--

1524
01:38:07,966 --> 01:38:10,302
It's that number! The missed calls.

1525
01:38:11,011 --> 01:38:12,470
Umbrella.

1526
01:38:13,430 --> 01:38:15,180
Finally, you answered.

1527
01:38:15,181 --> 01:38:19,226
You've called the phone of a man
who's gone missing.

1528
01:38:19,227 --> 01:38:21,146
Excuse me, but who are you?

1529
01:38:22,105 --> 01:38:24,648
I'm head of HR at Papyrus.

1530
01:38:24,649 --> 01:38:29,028
Mr. Go interviewed at our company,
and I called to say he was hired.

1531
01:38:29,029 --> 01:38:30,988
This is like some kind of curse.

1532
01:38:30,989 --> 01:38:32,114
What?

1533
01:38:32,115 --> 01:38:38,787
We originally planned to hire a different
applicant but couldn't reach him, either.

1534
01:38:38,788 --> 01:38:40,956
What was that man's name?

1535
01:38:40,957 --> 01:38:45,210
That man... hold on, his name...

1536
01:38:45,211 --> 01:38:46,754
He scored highest.

1537
01:38:46,755 --> 01:38:49,465
Gu... Gu... Gu...

1538
01:38:49,466 --> 01:38:51,216
Bummo.

1539
01:38:51,217 --> 01:38:55,387
And I knew I'd seen that name before.

1540
01:38:55,388 --> 01:38:56,473
GU BUMMO

1541
01:38:57,349 --> 01:38:58,725
Look, kiddo!

1542
01:39:01,561 --> 01:39:03,897
They knew each other?

1543
01:39:04,522 --> 01:39:05,731
Hm.

1544
01:39:05,732 --> 01:39:08,567
So, there were two paper men.

1545
01:39:08,568 --> 01:39:12,071
They knew each other.
And disappeared at the same time.

1546
01:39:12,072 --> 01:39:14,948
We did a painstaking search
around the car.

1547
01:39:14,949 --> 01:39:17,034
We found traces of Mr. Go's blood—

1548
01:39:17,035 --> 01:39:17,911
Blood...

1549
01:39:18,828 --> 01:39:23,541
And what might've caused
Mr. Go's blood to spill out of his veins?

1550
01:39:24,334 --> 01:39:25,918
- A gun.
- A handgun.

1551
01:39:25,919 --> 01:39:27,379
Made in North Korea.

1552
01:39:28,254 --> 01:39:30,047
- A bullet shell was found.
- [gasps]

1553
01:39:30,048 --> 01:39:30,882
By me.

1554
01:39:31,841 --> 01:39:33,551
[Man-su] A bullet shell!

1555
01:39:34,886 --> 01:39:36,388
[subtle grunt]

1556
01:39:38,723 --> 01:39:40,641
Pretty scary.

1557
01:39:40,642 --> 01:39:42,393
[somber cello music playing]

1558
01:39:42,394 --> 01:39:46,314
Until I catch the culprit,
you must be very careful.

1559
01:39:49,651 --> 01:39:51,360
[Man-su] Ri-one.

1560
01:39:51,361 --> 01:39:53,571
What kid listens to such music?

1561
01:39:54,948 --> 01:39:57,534
I'll contact you as soon as I go missing.

1562
01:39:58,493 --> 01:40:00,203
[chuckles]

1563
01:40:04,999 --> 01:40:07,794
This is not a joking matter.

1564
01:40:08,586 --> 01:40:09,713
Drive safely!

1565
01:40:10,463 --> 01:40:12,674
Ri-one! What are you doing?

1566
01:40:16,094 --> 01:40:17,636
[grunts]

1567
01:40:17,637 --> 01:40:19,096
- What's wrong?
- [crying]

1568
01:40:19,097 --> 01:40:20,889
My dear Ri-one...

1569
01:40:20,890 --> 01:40:25,227
[grunts] Don't cry... Don't cry.

1570
01:40:25,228 --> 01:40:26,395
Don't cry.

1571
01:40:26,396 --> 01:40:29,982
I'll bring them back, okay?
Stop crying.

1572
01:40:29,983 --> 01:40:32,025
[Ri-one continues crying]

1573
01:40:32,026 --> 01:40:34,028
Just need to do one more.

1574
01:40:35,113 --> 01:40:36,865
25 YEARS

1575
01:40:49,919 --> 01:40:51,921
[trot music playing]

1576
01:40:55,800 --> 01:40:58,635
[Sun-chul singing along]
♪ After you left me ♪

1577
01:40:58,636 --> 01:41:05,601
♪ The hole you left in my chest
Hurts me so much ♪

1578
01:41:05,602 --> 01:41:09,898
♪ Thinking I will die, I pray ♪

