Fifty-nine...

1842
02:01:21,066 --> 02:01:22,192
Sixty.

1843
02:01:27,030 --> 02:01:28,407
Mm.

1844
02:01:29,783 --> 02:01:31,451
[men laughing]

1845
02:01:32,995 --> 02:01:34,663
[man] That must've been hard for you.

1846
02:01:36,623 --> 02:01:42,503
So what I realized
while going through that ordeal

1847
02:01:42,504 --> 02:01:44,422
is you need a creative plan.

1848
02:01:44,423 --> 02:01:47,717
The important thing
is to shift your perspective.

1849
02:01:47,718 --> 02:01:50,678
In the execution phase,
you have to be persistent and bold.

1850
02:01:50,679 --> 02:01:55,058
When necessary, at any time
you need to be able to say no.

1851
02:01:55,851 --> 02:01:57,019
[ticking]

1852
02:02:06,361 --> 02:02:08,404
[man] We have a "lights-out system."

1853
02:02:08,405 --> 02:02:11,866
Recently we built
a fully automated factory.

1854
02:02:11,867 --> 02:02:13,075
Lights out?

1855
02:02:13,076 --> 02:02:16,495
- Since AI doesn't need lights turned on.
- Right.

1856
02:02:16,496 --> 02:02:21,083
The days of tapping a roll
with a stick are over.

1857
02:02:21,084 --> 02:02:22,877
Yes, of course.

1858
02:02:22,878 --> 02:02:25,713
Anyway, we quite urgently need you

1859
02:02:25,714 --> 02:02:27,798
to oversee this test run.

1860
02:02:27,799 --> 02:02:29,300
[Man-su] Uh...

1861
02:02:29,301 --> 02:02:32,804
When you say fully automated,
the workers...

1862
02:02:33,513 --> 02:02:36,307
...will have to be reduced, right?

1863
02:02:36,308 --> 02:02:39,686
That's the whole point of the system.
No other choice.

1864
02:02:40,270 --> 02:02:43,147
Do you have any objection?

1865
02:02:43,148 --> 02:02:45,901
[inaudible]

1866
02:02:49,488 --> 02:02:52,281
If you don't like it, you can say no.

1867
02:02:52,282 --> 02:02:54,325
[laughs] Not at all.

1868
02:02:54,326 --> 02:02:56,745
How can you go against the times?

1869
02:02:57,329 --> 02:03:04,002
But at any rate, you need one person
to watch over it all, right?

1870
02:03:08,256 --> 02:03:10,549
[detective] So five years ago,
there was a secret bid

1871
02:03:10,550 --> 02:03:12,177
at Minting and Security Printing Corp?

1872
02:03:12,886 --> 02:03:19,184
Yes, the competition was fierce then.

1873
02:03:20,393 --> 02:03:25,397
Solar, where I worked, was one of
the three designated companies.

1874
02:03:25,398 --> 02:03:28,735
We never even considered bidding.

1875
02:03:29,361 --> 02:03:31,862
Then who made the bid?

1876
02:03:31,863 --> 02:03:35,450
Two people facing off as representatives
of the two major paper companies.

1877
02:03:36,159 --> 02:03:41,081
Who were the rivals
in this bloody bidding war?

1878
02:03:43,959 --> 02:03:46,795
Gu Bummo and Go Sijo!

1879
02:03:47,754 --> 02:03:50,674
The day he returned
from his business trip to Daejeon...

1880
02:03:51,341 --> 02:03:54,386
His sleep-talking woke me up
in the middle of the night.

1881
02:03:56,054 --> 02:03:59,724
He started crying and whining,

1882
02:04:01,726 --> 02:04:06,231
saying things like "It's not fair!"
and "Don't insult me!"

1883
02:04:08,024 --> 02:04:09,359
Then after that,

1884
02:04:10,485 --> 02:04:11,945
wouldn't you know...

1885
02:04:12,487 --> 02:04:13,446
[imitates hawking]

1886
02:04:15,740 --> 02:04:17,951
He was surely asleep,

1887
02:04:18,577 --> 02:04:21,454
but he gathered the phlegm
in his mouth and...

1888
02:04:24,958 --> 02:04:26,001
[imitates spitting]

1889
02:04:27,169 --> 02:04:30,421
He spit on his own face.

1890
02:04:30,422 --> 02:04:31,339
[gasps]

1891
02:04:33,258 --> 02:04:35,176
It startled him too, and he woke up.

1892
02:04:35,177 --> 02:04:36,802
Ah.

1893
02:04:36,803 --> 02:04:38,637
The day he came back from Daejeon?

1894
02:04:38,638 --> 02:04:39,514
"It's so unfair"?

1895
02:04:41,850 --> 02:04:45,061
As you know, Minting and Security
Printing Corp is in Daejeon.

1896
02:04:46,146 --> 02:04:47,980
Ah.

1897
02:04:47,981 --> 02:04:49,858
Was that when it started?

1898
02:04:51,359 --> 02:04:55,779
He just listened to music here,
avoided going to bed with me.

1899
02:04:55,780 --> 02:05:01,327
After he got fired,
he drank all day, developed depression...

1900
02:05:01,328 --> 02:05:02,913
[gasps] Oh, my God.

1901
02:05:04,247 --> 02:05:06,333
He didn't bring his medication.

1902
02:05:08,043 --> 02:05:09,043
[sniffles]

1903
02:05:09,044 --> 02:05:10,045
Honey,

1904
02:05:10,837 --> 02:05:12,630
where in the world are you?

1905
02:05:12,631 --> 02:05:15,800
Does your husband own
a handgun by any chance?

1906
02:05:23,141 --> 02:05:25,769
Can I ask why you took so long to answer?

1907
02:05:28,688 --> 02:05:32,400
If you own a firearm,
you need to report it, right?

1908
02:05:33,443 --> 02:05:34,777
He didn't do that.

1909
02:05:34,778 --> 02:05:36,029
What's more,

1910
02:05:37,614 --> 02:05:39,616
it vanished with my husband.

1911
02:05:40,367 --> 02:05:41,785
He could...

1912
02:05:42,911 --> 02:05:44,495
commit suicide with it.

1913
02:05:44,496 --> 02:05:46,623
[gasps] Please find him quickly.

1914
02:05:48,416 --> 02:05:49,501
[sobs]

1915
02:05:51,503 --> 02:05:53,171
Was it one of these?

1916
02:06:11,064 --> 02:06:12,315
This one?

1917
02:06:20,198 --> 02:06:21,573
[exhales]

1918
02:06:21,574 --> 02:06:24,744
Gu Bummo's wife really said that?

1919
02:06:26,705 --> 02:06:30,082
So be wary of Gu Bummo.

1920
02:06:30,083 --> 02:06:31,501
Remember his face.

1921
02:06:35,672 --> 02:06:40,343
Gu Bummo killed Go Sijo and ran away?

1922
02:06:41,678 --> 02:06:44,680
Wow, this is...

1923
02:06:44,681 --> 02:06:46,182
[Man-su sighs]

1924
02:06:49,728 --> 02:06:50,603
Huh.

1925
02:06:52,689 --> 02:06:54,482
[exhales]

1926
02:06:56,276 --> 02:06:57,401
Wow.

1927
02:06:57,402 --> 02:06:58,820
[Man-su] Honey!

1928
02:07:01,573 --> 02:07:03,241
Got something to say?

1929
02:07:08,204 --> 02:07:10,749
Congrats on your first day at work.

1930
02:07:14,878 --> 02:07:17,046
This weekend, should we do a pig roast?

1931
02:07:17,047 --> 02:07:17,922
- No.
- No way!

1932
02:07:23,428 --> 02:07:27,182
It's too cold for that now.

1933
02:07:28,975 --> 02:07:33,479
Quit the clinic and take up tennis again.
I'll buy you a new racket.

1934
02:07:33,480 --> 02:07:35,690
I'm not doing that anymore.

1935
02:07:36,441 --> 02:07:37,817
I'll save money.

1936
02:07:42,238 --> 02:07:44,156
Si-two, Ri-two, house!

1937
02:07:44,157 --> 02:07:45,325
House!

1938
02:07:47,786 --> 02:07:50,205
Ri-one, come here! Don't play over there.

1939
02:07:51,122 --> 02:07:53,332
[Ri-one] A snail! A snail!

1940
02:07:53,333 --> 02:07:55,293
[Miri] I called the real estate agent.

1941
02:07:56,378 --> 02:07:57,587
Said we'll keep the house.

1942
02:07:58,421 --> 02:07:59,797
Oh.

1943
02:07:59,798 --> 02:08:03,258
[Miri] We planted an apple tree here,
how can we sell it?

1944
02:08:03,259 --> 02:08:05,095
[Man-su] Exactly.

1945
02:08:06,221 --> 02:08:08,056
Ri-one!

1946
02:08:09,015 --> 02:08:10,183
Ri-one!

1947
02:08:11,226 --> 02:08:12,894
I'll see you later.

1948
02:08:16,898 --> 02:08:20,276
Bugs are eating it alive.

1949
02:08:27,367 --> 02:08:30,369
[reporter] …will ease up
sometime this morning.

1950
02:08:30,370 --> 02:08:33,622
After the nighttime rain which
seemed to mourn the passing of autumn,

1951
02:08:33,623 --> 02:08:38,378
the temperature also dropped sharply,
bringing us one step closer to winter.

1952
02:08:47,429 --> 02:08:49,431
[footsteps approaching]

1953
02:08:52,392 --> 02:08:55,269
- Going to school already?
- Dongho and I are meeting early.

1954
02:08:55,270 --> 02:08:57,855
Are you two still friends?

1955
02:08:57,856 --> 02:09:01,317
- Even after what happened last...
- [dramatic cello music playing]

1956
